<br>
Enchanters don't have a good damage/mana ratio, so root/nuke tactics are not particularly feasable.  Enchanter summoned pets are weak tanks that grow progressively weaker compared to the mobs as the Enchanter levels.  They get quite beat up against even one debuffed blue con enemy, and the Enchanter can't heal the animation.<br>
<br>
The Charming spells are arguably the best soloing tactic as that's probably the best way to do decent damage.  They can be quite effective with a judicious use of root spells to stick down the monster you're fighting.  But when things go badly with Charming they often go very, very badly, and that can sour an Enchanter on using that tactic.  Bards are somewhat more sturdy Charmers that can at least run away with Selo's when something goes wrong.  An Enchanter may have a problem in mezzing multiple mobs hitting them at once (i.e: broken charm and unrooted enemy).<br>
<br>
Duoing is a different thing altogether; Enchanters are pretty good there, especially if paired with someone that does some decent damage.  But I wouldn't recommend Enchanter as a solo class to anyone that's not an experienced player.<br>
<br>
Just the two cents of one relative newbie to EQ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufuffindmuffin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fuffin D Muffin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/02 6:55:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2954.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Classes</span><hr size=1> Charm soloing is the only way to go - if people use the net to find resources on how to go about it, it wouldn't be much of a problem for them to grasp. Took me a while but now I have no doubt that there is no better way to solo with any other class. With all the benefits Enchanters get in terms of crowd control / buffs / debuffs it all becomes relatively easy to solo any amount of mobs at any certain time. <br>
<br>
It is a difficult task for a while, but due to its strength around level 35 - 40+, definitely shouldn't be a class to go unmentioned when it comes to solo capabilities.  <p><img src="http://kektik.com.au/miscpics/fufsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unoirdaila.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Noirdaila</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Troublemaker</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/02 7:20:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2954.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Classes</span><hr size=1> I have met (not to say there arent other, but, I havent grouped with them to know if this is true...) 2 enchanters that IMHO are the best I have ever seen.  They both leveled primarily soloing &amp; know their spells in &amp; out.  When you dont have to sit on your butt casting slow/speed...you become reliant on other spells to help you &amp; you get to know those spells quite a bit better. As a cleric, I grouped with a chanter (and JUST a chanter) a few times (on my other server) and I have to say, I never healed him.  I was there for damage, thats IT. &quot;IF&quot; it had gotten bad, I was there to heal, or maybe rez...but he knew his stuff inside &amp; out, &amp; upside down too.  I never knew chanters could do that kind of stuff.  It was amazing! He held the whole giant fort in BW with NP...sill yme, I thought chanters were a weak caster class!  Since then, I have found only ONE other chanter that could do it as well &amp; I never get tired of watching him (my RL husband plays a chanter, BTW <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
I think ANY class can benefit from learning to solo, and from hunting with unusual partners.  My absolute favorite combo to group with is my cleric &amp; a SK....next would be a chanter, then a BL...full groups are great, but if its just 2...thats what I look for.  Its a bit of a challenge when I have to play healer, buffer, nuker &amp; crowd controll, but, I learned a lot &amp; so did everyone else!<br>
<br>
