<br>
Druid (hate to admit it but the buggers have that quadkiting thing)<br>
Necromancers (best DoTs ingame, very strong pet, lifetaps, lich line of spells)<br>
Shamen (excellent DoTs, ability to wear chain for decent ac, heals/buffs/pets post 39)<br>
Beastlords (strong balance of melee and spells, strong pet, strong pet heals)<br>
Wizards (can quad but have no sow to up their speed, unless they are jbooted, great at nuking)<br>
Bards (selos, bard kiting)<br>
Shadowknights (strong melee class, debuffs/lifetaps/pets, good hp/ac)<br>
Mages (strong pet, fast nukes)<br>
Paladins (good hp/ac, good melee ability, heals/buffs/root, very good vs undead)<br>
Enchanters (charm soloing, risky but sometimes very effective if done properly)<br>
<br>
the rest such as rogues, warriors and clerics are pretty much left out when solo ability comes to call, but they have excellent skills for group hunting which balances it out<br>
<br>
<br>
